<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued February 21 at 3:32PM EST until February 22 at 12:00PM EST by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS
EVENING TO NOON EST TUESDAY...
* WHAT...Freezing rain expected. Total ice accumulations of around
one tenth to two tenths of an inch.
* WHERE...Tuscola, Saginaw, Huron, Bay and Midland Counties.
* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to noon EST Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Hazardous travel conditions on untreated roads. The
hazardous conditions could impact the morning commute. Light
icing on trees, power lines, and other outdoor objects.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Patchy freezing drizzle or light freezing
rain develops this evening with the greatest coverage and
intensity between 10 PM and 6 AM.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.</instruction>
